<p class="eyebrow">Support / Voice / Phone / Poly Edge</p>
<h1>Configure Poly Edge for VoiceTel.</h1>
<p class="lede">Poly's Edge B and Edge E series replaced the VVX line for new deployments. They run Poly OS (formerly UC Software 7.x), which uses a redesigned web UI compared to VVX. The fields are largely the same; the menu paths differ.</p>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>If you have a VVX, see the older guide</h2>
	<p>VVX 250/350/450/601 phones use UC Software 6.x with the legacy <strong>Settings → Lines</strong> menu structure documented separately at <a href="/support/voice/phone/polycom/">Poly / Polycom (VVX)</a>.</p>
</section>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>Web UI configuration</h2>
	<ol>
		<li>Find the IP: <strong>Settings → Status → Network</strong>.</li>
		<li>Open <code>https://&lt;phone-ip&gt;</code>. Sign in (default password printed on the device's bottom label or the box; change immediately).</li>
		<li>Click <strong>Lines</strong> in the top navigation.</li>
		<li>Select <strong>Line 1</strong>.</li>
		<li>Identity section:
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Display Name:</strong> caller's name</li>
				<li><strong>Address:</strong> <code>sip:&lt;sip-username&gt;@&lt;sip-host-from-portal&gt;</code></li>
				<li><strong>Authentication User ID:</strong> SIP username from VoiceTel onboarding</li>
				<li><strong>Authentication Password:</strong> SIP password</li>
				<li><strong>Label:</strong> short label shown on the line key</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>Server section:
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Address:</strong> the SIP server host shown in your customer portal</li>
				<li><strong>Port:</strong> 5060</li>
				<li><strong>Transport:</strong> UDP only</li>
				<li><strong>Expires:</strong> 360</li>
				<li><strong>Register:</strong> Enabled</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>Click <strong>Save</strong>.</li>
		<li>Open <strong>SIP → Local Settings</strong>:
			<ul>
				<li><strong>NAT Keep-Alive Interval:</strong> 30</li>
				<li><strong>Keep-Alive Method:</strong> rport</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>Save. The line registers within a few seconds.</li>
	</ol>
</section>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>Codec preference</h2>
	<p>Open <strong>Audio → Codec Profiles → Audio Codec Priority</strong>. Enable PCMU, PCMA, and G.729 in that order.</p>
</section>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>Auto-provisioning</h2>
	<p>Poly ZTP works for Edge phones the same way as VVX. Register your MAC ranges at <code>https://ztp.poly.com</code> and point ZTP at your VoiceTel provisioning URL. Edge phones boot, contact ZTP, redirect, fetch their config, register.</p>
	<p>Self-hosted provisioning: Edge phones look for <code>000000000000.cfg</code> + per-MAC <code>&lt;mac&gt;.cfg</code> via TFTP/HTTP/HTTPS — same shape as VVX, but the config schema has new keys for Poly OS features. Contact VoiceTel engineering for an Edge-specific template.</p>
</section>

<aside class="cta-block" aria-labelledby="poly-edge-cta-heading">
	<h2 id="poly-edge-cta-heading">Migrating VVX → Edge fleet?</h2>
	<p>Edge phones import most VVX provisioning XML, but a few keys (line registration, codec profiles) changed. VoiceTel engineering can review your existing VVX template and adapt for Edge.</p>
